8 65–6.
9 (a) (1) [Said Drummond Citizens’ Committee] THE VILLAGE COUNCIL is
10 empowered to ESTABLISH, OPERATE, MAINTAIN, AND CONTROL ALL PUBLIC WAYS IN
11 THE VILLAGE EXCEPT THE PUBLIC WAYS UNDER THE JURISDICTION OF THE STATE,
12 INCLUDING BY REQUIRING THE OWNERS OF PROPERTY ABUTTING A STREET, ROAD,
13 OR LANE TO REMOVE ICE, SNOW, DIRT, DEBRIS, OR OTHER OBSTRUCTIONS AS WELL
14 AS ANY OTHER ACTION NECESSARY FOR THE PUBLIC HEALTH OR SAFETY,
15 CONSTRUCT A NEW STREET, ROAD, OR LANE, grade, pave, macadamize or otherwise
16 improve any existing street, road or lane, or any street, road or lane which has been or may
17 be acquired and opened for public use, and to lay sidewalks [and], curbs, AND GUTTERS
18 thereon[; provided, that said Drummond Citizens’ Committee].
19 (2) THE VILLAGE COUNCIL, subject to the approval of the [county
20 council] COUNTY COUNCIL and after petition of residents and hearing, as hereinafter
