22 CONSTRUCTING, grading, paving, macadamizing or improving against the property
23 abutting on [said] A street, road or lane, or sidewalk, in proportion to the frontage of [said]
24 THE abutting property on the [same; provided, further, that upon] STREET, ROAD OR
25 LANE, OR SIDEWALK.
26 (3) ON the petition in writing of two–thirds of the residents owning
27 property abutting upon any street, road or lane to be CONSTRUCTED, graded, paved,
28 macadamized or otherwise to be improved under the provisions of this section requesting
29 the CONSTRUCTING, grading, paving, macadamizing or otherwise improving of [such]
30 THE streets, roads or lanes, it shall be the duty of the [Drummond Citizens’ Committee]
31 VILLAGE COUNCIL to make the [said] assessment against the abutting property to
32 provide the funds for and cause to be performed the necessary work or construction to be
33 done in accordance with the provisions herein provided[; and provided, further, that
34 before].
35 (4) BEFORE any contract for work shall be entered into, or any obligation
36 with respect [thereto] TO THE CONTRACT incurred, notice shall be given to the owners

