10 (b) (1) Any tax so assessed, as above provided in this section, shall be payable
11 to [the county treasurer] MONTGOMERY COUNTY in from four (4) to ten (10) semiannual
12 installments, as nearly equal as may be, the first installment thereof to become due and
13 payable within six (6) months after the levy of [said] THE special tax as above provided,
14 and each of the other [said] installments within six (6) months after the preceding one (1)
15 shall have become due[; each].
16 (2) EACH installment of [said] THE tax shall become a lien against [said]
17 THE abutting property and shall bear interest from the date of levy thereof at the rate of
18 six (6) per centum per annum until paid[;] or [said] THE tax may be paid in full without
19 interest during the first installment period[, and if].
20 (3) IF any of [said] THE installments [thereof be] OF THE TAX ARE not
21 paid within thirty (30) days after [same] THE INSTALLMENT shall have become due, the
22 entire amount of [said] THE tax assessed to the person [or persons] or corporation in
23 default, with interest, shall [thereupon] THEN become due and payable, and may be
24 collected in the same manner provided in the act for the collection of unpaid taxes. [And
25 the said Drummond Citizens’ Committee]
26 (4) THE VILLAGE COUNCIL shall have the power to prescribe the number
27 of semiannual installments in which the tax [so assessed, as above provided,] shall be
28 payable.
29 (c) All money so received by [said county treasurer] THE COUNTY shall, [upon]
30 ON order of [said county council] THE COUNTY COUNCIL, be paid over to the treasurer of
31 [said] THE Village [of Drummond, and the said Drummond Citizens’ Committee shall
32 become charged with the duty of paving, grading, macadamizing or otherwise improving
