20 (A) THE VILLAGE COUNCIL SHALL APPOINT:
21 (1) A MAYOR, WHO SHALL PRESIDE OVER MEETINGS OF THE VILLAGE
22 COUNCIL AND SERVE AS THE CHIEF EXECUTIVE OF THE VILLAGE;
23 (2) A TREASURER, WHO SHALL ASSIST IN THE PREPARATION OF THE
24 ANNUAL BUDGET AND SUPERVISE THE DISBURSEMENT OF PUBLIC FUNDS;
25 (3) A SECRETARY, WHO SHALL ASSIST IN THE KEEPING OF RECORDS
26 OF THE VILLAGE COUNCIL; AND
27 (4) OTHER OFFICERS AND EMPLOYEES, WHO SHALL HOLD TERMS AND
28 WHO SHALL HAVE DUTIES ESTABLISHED BY THE VILLAGE COUNCIL.
29 (B) The [said treasurer and other] officers AND EMPLOYEES of [said] THE
30 Village [of Drummond] shall hold their offices or positions at the pleasure of [said
31 Drummond Citizens’ Committee or in conformity with contracts which may be made by and
32 between said committee and such officers and employees, for a period not to extend beyond
33 the limits of the terms of office of said committee] THE VILLAGE COUNCIL.

HOUSE BILL 1623 9
1 (C) (1) THE OFFICERS AND EMPLOYEES OF THE VILLAGE SHALL GIVE
2 BOND TO THE VILLAGE IN AN AMOUNT AND WITH SURETY DETERMINED BY THE
3 VILLAGE COUNCIL.
4 (2) THE PREMIUMS OF FIDELITY BONDS OWED BY OFFICERS AND
5 EMPLOYEES OF THE VILLAGE SHALL BE PAID BY THE VILLAGE.
6 65–8.
7 (A) [Said Drummond Citizens’ Committee shall] THE VILLAGE COUNCIL MAY
8 not expend for material or work [in connection with anyone undertaking] a sum exceeding
9 [three hundred dollars ($300.00)] FIFTEEN THOUSAND DOLLARS ($15,000), OR THE
10 AMOUNT FOR WHICH PUBLICATION OF NOTICE OF PROCUREMENT IS REQUIRED BY
11 STATE LAW, WHICHEVER IS GREATER, without having first advertised the specifications
12 [therefor] and inviting bids [for the same], after which [said committee] THE VILLAGE
13 COUNCIL may purchase [such] THE material or make contract for [such] THE work, or
14 have [such] THE work done by employing labor, or otherwise, as it may deem best.
15 (B) NOTWITHSTANDING ANY OTHER PROVISION TO THE CONTRARY, THE
16 VILLAGE COUNCIL MAY CONTRACT FOR MATERIAL OR WORK WITHOUT FIRST
17 HAVING INVITED BIDS IF:
18 (1) THE CONTRACT AWARD SERVES A PUBLIC PURPOSE AND THERE IS
19 ONLY ONE SOURCE FOR THE REQUIRED MATERIAL TO MEET THE NEEDS OF THE
20 VILLAGE;
21 (2) THE CONTRACT IS IN CONNECTION WITH POTENTIAL OR PENDING
22 LITIGATION, CONDEMNATION, OR COLLECTIVE BARGAINING;
23 (3) A PROPOSED CONTRACTOR OR SUBCONTRACTOR HAS BEEN
24 SPECIFICALLY IDENTIFIED IN A GRANT ACCEPTED BY THE VILLAGE;
25 (4) A PROPOSED CONTRACTOR OR SUBCONTRACTOR HAS BEEN
26 SELECTED THROUGH A COMPETITIVE BIDDING PROCESS UNDERTAKEN BY A STATE,
27 COUNTY, OR MUNICIPAL CORPORATION, OR COOPERATIVELY WITH THE VILLAGE,
28 AND SUBSTANTIALLY SIMILAR TERMS ARE OFFERED TO THE VILLAGE;
29 (5) THE SERVICES ARE PROFESSIONAL IN NATURE, INCLUDING
30 ACCOUNTING, ARCHITECTURE, AUDITING, ENGINEERING, LEGAL, OR SURVEYING
31 SERVICES; OR
32 (6) THERE EXISTS A THREAT TO THE PUBLIC HEALTH, SAFETY, OR
33 WELFARE OR WHERE DELAY WOULD SERIOUSLY INJURE THE VILLAGE FINANCIALLY
34 OR OTHERWISE.

